{"title": "Adam Bede", "description": "Adam Bede, the first novel written by George Eliot (the pen name of Mary Ann Evans), was published in 1859. It was published pseudonymously, even though Evans was a well-published and highly respected scholar of her time. The novel has remained in print ever since, and is used in university studies of 19th century English literature.<br /><br />\nThe story's plot follows four characters rural lives in the fictional community of Hayslope\u2014a rural, pastoral and close-knit community in 1799. The novel revolves around a love triangle between beautiful but thoughtless Hetty Sorrel, Captain Arthur Donnithorne, the young squire who seduces her, Adam Bede, her unacknowledged lover, and Dinah Morris, Hetty's cousin, a fervent Methodist lay preacher.<br />\n(Summary Wikipedia)", "duration": 74087, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "739", "name": "George Eliot"}], "coverArt": "https://www.archive.org/download/LibrivoxCdCoverArt15/Adam_Bede_1202.jpg", "copyright_year": "1859", "genres": ["Romance"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "LibriVox Volunteers"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Alex Buie"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Lucy Burgoyne (1950 - 2014)"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Nathalie J."}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "Book 1, Chapter 1:The Workshop", "readers": [23], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/adam_bede_0901_librivox/adambede_01_eliot_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1225}, {"section": 2, "title": "Book 1, Chapter 2: The Preaching", "readers": [1061], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/adam_bede_0901_librivox/adambede_02_eliot_64kb.mp3", "duration": 2631}, {"section": 3, "title": "Book 1, Chapter 3: After the Preaching", "readers": [681], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/adam_bede_0901_librivox/adambede_03_eliot_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1128}, {"section": 4, "title": "Book 1, Chapter 4: Home and Its Sorrows", "readers": [1061], "path": "https://www.archive